@node "System" "System requirements"
@{b}System requirements@{ub}

  Minimal requirements:
  ---------------------

  · an Amiga
  · playerprefs.library
  · debox.library
  · OS2.04 
 

  Recommended:
  ------------

  · a 68020 or better
  · Harddrive
  · OS3.1

@endnode

@node "faq" "FAQ"
@{b}F.A.Q.@{ub}

 This section contains some frequently asked questions about the
 CDTVTools. If you cannot find help for your problem here, please
 don't hesitate to @{"contact" link autor} me. 

 Q.: After I started a commodity, how can I remove or control it then?
 A.: You have to use the program "Exchange" which is located in your
     Tools/Commodities drawer.
     
 Q.: I started the CDPlayer first with the inbuilt faked device and
     now I added the tooltype CX_NOFAKEDEVICE to make the program use
     my CD-ROM filesystem's cdtv.device. I started it but it still
     does not work!?
 A.: The faked device is still in memory. Open a shell and execute
     "Avail FLUSH" or reboot your machine.
     
 Q.: A commodity says that I would be using a wrong version of the
     playerprefs.library!?
 A.: Please copy the playerprefs.library provided with this archive
     to your libs: and flush the libs or reboot! It should work then.
     Some CDTV emulators put fake playerprefs.library in libs:. Those
     do not work then of course.
    
 Q.: What does F.A.Q. mean?
 A.: Frequently asked questions.

 Q.: I can't beat the dragon in Tomb Raider 2.
 A.: ...
  
@endnode

